      <description>&lt;div class=&#34;lead text-neutral-500 dark:text-neutral-400 !mb-9 text-xl&#34;&gt;
  The financial term &amp;lsquo;No-arbitrage&amp;rsquo; is also a pricing approach, upon which Black-Scholes-Merton (BSM) model was developed. It assumes that there are no risk-free profit opportunities in the market.
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the realm of asset valuation, several primary approaches and methodologies are employed to determine an asset&amp;rsquo;s fair value.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
